                  <li class="program-course">
            <a href="/study/2014-2015/courses/jwst-546" class="program-course-title">
              JWST 546 Innovative Medieval Parshanut (3 credits)              <!---->            </a>
            <div class="program-course-description">
              <div class="program-course-description-inner">
                <div id="node-29002" class=" clearfix">
  
  
  
  <div class="meta">
    <p>Offered by: Jewish Studies (<a href="/study/2014-2015/node/607">Faculty of Arts</a>)</p>
      </div>

  <div class="content">
    <h3>Overview</h3>

    <p>
      Jewish Studies              : The dynamics of Jewish Bible interpretation in medieval times and the attempts by various authors to read the Bible as an independent Hebrew document, not only in the light of the pre-medieval rabbinical exegetical tradition.          </p>

    <p class="catalog-terms">
